  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\nPrincipal Component Analysis finds the directions of maximum variance in\na dataset.  It is one of the most widely used techniques for\n**dimensionality reduction**: by projecting data onto the top few principal\ncomponents, we can capture most of the information in fewer dimensions.\n\nThe key insight is that the **covariance matrix** encodes all the\nvariance structure.  Its eigenvectors point along the principal\ndirections and its eigenvalues measure the variance along each one.\n\nIn this notebook we:\n1. Generate 2D data with a known elongated, rotated structure\n2. Compute the covariance matrix with `np_cov`\n3. Find principal components via eigendecomposition with `np_eig`\n4. Project, visualize, and reconstruct the data",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 1,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Generating 2D Data with Known Structure\n\nWe create an elongated cloud of points rotated at 30 degrees.  The data\nis generated along two orthogonal \"true\" principal axes with very\ndifferent variances ($\\sigma_1 = 3$, $\\sigma_2 = 0.5$), then rotated\nby the angle $\\theta = \\pi/6$ into the $x$-$y$ plane.\n\nThis gives us ground truth to verify that PCA recovers the correct\ndirections and variance magnitudes.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "n : 200$\nangle : float(%pi/6)$   /* 30 degrees */\n\n/* Generate data along the true principal axes */\npc1 : np_scale(3.0, np_randn([n]))$   /* high variance axis */\npc2 : np_scale(0.5, np_randn([n]))$   /* low variance axis */\n\n/* Rotate into x-y coordinates */\nx : np_add(np_scale(cos(angle), pc1), np_scale(-sin(angle), pc2))$\ny : np_add(np_scale(sin(angle), pc1), np_scale(cos(angle), pc2))$\n\nprint(\"Generated\", n, \"points with sigma1=3, sigma2=0.5, angle=30 deg\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 2,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Generated 200 points with sigma1=3, sigma2=0.5, angle=30 deg"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Plot the raw data */\nax_draw2d(\n  marker_size=4, opacity=0.5,\n  points(x, y),\n  title=\"Original Data\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\",\n  aspect_ratio=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 3,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "application/x-maxima-plotly": [
