49997078988,-0.5832479824315457,1.7711961908828855,-2.6628686583515937,-1.205621310310848,0.5348921035508242,-0.9580773175931454,0.5128698352740716,-4.158472756508926,0.7956168033056229,-1.0673897483676342,2.470492115244997,-0.9649112283391528,0.1434748491319603,0.25599716177070897,0.7895894757973458,1.4398855948272098,-1.2650626419063724,-0.8273296763465215,3.5211147515068126,-0.1902391831322119,-1.9031916609249209,0.5324174235368833,-2.0078126137356302,2.5349092648052425,-1.5977814579068192,-0.7765913996739428,2.470071149960271,-0.26362566268396054,-1.4938049232402588,-1.317390792836293,1.866789118548231,-1.4469299082680012,-1.0977004078361785,-1.6227166835868965,-0.1344947910002679,-1.9888995999729426,0.36952991097708643,-0.21419975466434737,-2.7401792417531237,-0.5616969156321032,0.0036029652474872664,-2.0720233966272406,1.6394993114098206,3.0040609943053744,1.424482749084924,-1.553235462124298,0.21873080173941656,-2.7655284875807284,-0.19093964815380718,-1.8420824339634165,-0.2689026784207538,1.3361592109451352,-1.0264319385550522,-0.34055428513692776,-1.7862931195733134,0.0853783711098802,-2.4454170896770404,-2.628499741053331,0.7797392150063847,-0.7865494816729754,0.06444651586690442,1.2642194505704796,-1.257019002296548,1.8649546272707829,-1.6666415649566122,2.655763416700164,-1.167885207144691,1.779466913016797,2.351483932185768,-3.354256927672112,0.3495894320407111,2.0479879111910066,-3.414307371613637,0.11775502392060228,2.568306846675621,-3.0341935612589372,-0.6965475713575339,-0.24191102848510856,1.598207191218689,-1.9341880921367494,-0.9461873733950084,-3.3953336649328216,-0.4711266985658079,0.3132992766070115,1.4886761756095677,0.843643918157073,-0.9989080666878268,1.4299585024142174,0.1799206889876037,2.249371786308014,1.41476809646846],\"type\":\"scatter\",\"mode\":\"markers\",\"marker\":{\"size\":4},\"opacity\":0.5,\"name\":\"points\"}],\"layout\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Original Data\"},\"width\":700,\"height\":700,\"plot_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"paper_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"xaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"x\"},\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1},\"yaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"y\"},\"scaleanchor\":\"x\",\"scaleratio\":1,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1}}}"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Computing the Covariance Matrix\n\nThe covariance matrix $C$ summarizes how each pair of variables co-varies.\nFor our 2D data (stacked as an $n \\times 2$ matrix), $C$ is $2 \\times 2$:\n\n$$C = \\frac{1}{n-1} \\sum_{i=1}^{n} (\\mathbf{x}_i - \\bar{\\mathbf{x}})(\\mathbf{x}_i - \\bar{\\mathbf{x}})^T$$\n\nThe diagonal entries are the variances of $x$ and $y$; the off-diagonal\nentries are the covariance between them.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Stack x, y into an n-by-2 matrix */\ndata : np_hstack(\n  np_reshape(x, [n, 1]),\n  np_reshape(y, [n, 1])\n)$\nprint(\"Data shape:\", np_shape(data))$\n\n/* Compute the sample covariance matrix */\nC : np_cov(data)$\nprint(\"Covariance matrix:\")$\nnp_to_matrix(C);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 4,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Data shape: [200,2]\nCovariance matrix:"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi 7.3784592820210895&4.226453325702441\\cr 4.226453325702441&2.7545220424376584\\cr\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 4,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Eigendecomposition\n\nThe eigenvalues of the covariance matrix give the variance along each\nprincipal component, and the eigenvectors give the directions.  The\neigenvector with the largest eigenvalue points along the direction of\ngreatest spread in the data.\n\nWe sort the eigenvalues in descending order so that PC1 always\ncorresponds to the dominant component.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Eigendecomposition of the covariance matrix */\n[vals, vecs] : np_eig(C)$\n\n/* Sort by descending eigenvalue so PC1 = dominant component */\nif np_ref(vals, 0) < np_ref(vals, 1) then (\n  vals : ndarray([np_ref(vals, 1), np_ref(vals, 0)], [2]),\n  vecs : np_hstack(np_col(vecs, 1), np_col(vecs, 0))\n)$\n\nprint(\"Eigenvalues (descending):\")$\nprint(np_to_list(vals))$\n\nprint(\"Eigenvectors (columns):\")$\nnp_to_matrix(vecs);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 5,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Eigenvalues (descending):\n[9.883969942230777,0.24901138222797123]\nEigenvectors (columns):"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi 0.8602071028781854&-0.5099448403091447\\cr 0.5099448403091447&0.8602071028781854\\cr\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 5,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Explained variance ratio: fraction of total variance per component */\nlam : np_to_list(vals)$\ntotal_var : lsum(v, v, lam)$\nratios : map(lambda([v], v / total_var), lam)$\n\nprint(\"Explained variance ratios:\")$\nfor i : 1 thru length(ratios) do\n  printf(true, \"  PC~d: ~,1f%~%\", i, ratios[i] * 100)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 6,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Explained variance ratios:\n  PC1: 97.5%o144\no144  PC2: 2.5%o144\no144$$\\mathbf{done}$$\nfalse"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Visualizing Principal Components\n\nWe overlay the eigenvectors on the scatter plot, scaled by the square\nroot of the corresponding eigenvalue (so the arrow length is proportional\nto the standard deviation along that direction).  The longer arrow should\npoint along the elongated direction of the cloud.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Compute the mean of x and y for centering the arrows */\nmx : np_mean(x)$\nmy : np_mean(y)$\n\n/* Extract eigenvectors and scale by sqrt(eigenvalue) */\nev1 : np_to_list(np_col(vecs, 0))$\nev2 : np_to_list(np_col(vecs, 1))$\nscale1 : sqrt(lam[1])$\nscale2 : sqrt(lam[2])$\n\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"steelblue\", marker_size=4, opacity=0.4,\n  points(x, y),\n  /* First eigenvector (larger variance — dominant PC) */\n  color=\"darkred\", line_width=3,\n  lines([mx, mx + scale1 * ev1[1]], [my, my + scale1 * ev1[2]]),\n  /* Second eigenvector (smaller variance) */\n  color=\"red\", line_width=3,\n  lines([mx, mx + scale2 * ev2[1]], [my, my + scale2 * ev2[2]]),\n  title=\"Data with Principal Component Directions\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\",\n  aspect_ratio=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 7,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
